assertor.title: QualWeb
assertor.description: QualWeb is an automatic accessibility evaluator for webpages.

test.title: Document has a landmark with non-repeated content
test.description: This rule checks that each page has an element with a landmark semantic role starting with non-repeated content

result.description:
Check either there is no non-repeated content after repeated content or there exists an element for which all the following are true:
               - the element has semantic role inheriting from landmark; and
               - the first perceivable content (in tree order in the flat tree) which is an inclusive descendant of the element is non-repeated content after repeated content; and
               - the element is included in the accessibility tree.

test.title: Document has heading for non-repeated content
test.description: This rule checks that the non-repeated content contains a heading

result.description:
Check either there is no non-repeated content after repeated content or there exists an element for which all the following are true:
               - the element is non-repeated content after repeated content; and
               - the element has a semantic role of heading; and
               - the element is visible; and
               - the element is included in the accessibility tree.

test.title: Block of repeated content is collapsible
test.description: This rule checks that repeated blocks of content are collapsible.

result.description:
For each block of repeated content in each test target, which is before (in the flat tree) at least one node of non-repeated content after repeated content, all the following are true:
               - there exists an instrument to make all nodes in this block not visible; and
               - there exists an instrument to remove all nodes in this block from the accessibility tree.

test.title: Document has an instrument to move focus to non-repeated content
test.description: This rule checks that there is an instrument to move focus to non-repeated content in the page.

result.description:
Check if the page has any instrument(s) to move focus. 
            Check if any of these instrument(s) is being used before a block of repeated content, and the focus is moved to just before a block of non-repeated content.

test.title: Bypass Blocks of Repeated Content
test.description: This rule checks that each page has a mechanism to bypass repeated blocks of content.

result.description: The rule can't tell because of the rule QW-ACT-R63
